parameters: \n<Minato>\F[\V[2]]\FF[61]\AA[F]...A job for me to appear in a movie?

\n<Sonoda>\FF[61]\F[\V[2]]\AA[FF]Ah... It seems that Director Udo Takeru personally
requested \C[27].
バンドメンバー

\n<Sawa>\FF[61]\F[\V[2]]\AA[FF]Wow... That's amazing. Director Udo is famous for horror
movies, right?
バンドメンバー
\n<Momo>\FF[61]\F[\V[2]]\AA[FF]Yeah, yeah, that hairstyle is cool, isn't it?
バンドメンバー
\n<Kino>\FF[61]\F[\V[2]]\AA[FF]That's not it... but isn't it a good story?

\n<Minato>\F[\V[2]]\FF[61]\AA[F]Being specifically chosen... But I don't have any
connection with Director Udo, do I? Isn't this a
mistake, like a request for a theme song?

\n<Sonoda>\FF[61]\F[\V[2]]\AA[FF]I made sure to confirm that. It seems that they
want you to participate as an actress, not as a
rock musician.

\n<Sonoda>\FF[61]\F[\V[2]]\AA[FF]And... it's not like we have absolutely no connection.
We met in front of the elevator after the meeting
three days ago, right?
\n<Minato>\F[\V[2]]\FF[61]\AA[F](That man who gave me a lewd gaze back then...)

\n<Minato>\F[\V[2]]\FF[61]\AA[F]...Isn't it suspicious? In terms of acting, I'm a complete
amateur, you know?

\n<Sonoda>\FF[61]\F[\V[2]]\AA[FF]Should I stick with my current style... or should I try
something new... It may sound cold, but... it's up
to you to decide what you want to do.
バンドメンバー

\n<Kino>\FF[61]\F[\V[2]]\AA[FF]You should give it a try! I want to see Minato's
acting!
バンドメンバー
\n<Momo>\FF[61]\F[\V[2]]\AA[FF]Nene-chan making her actress debut... I'm so jealous...
バンドメンバー

\n<Sawa>\FF[61]\F[\V[2]]\AA[FF]Why don't you give it a try? I think it's a good
opportunity...

\F[\V[2]]\FF[61]\AA[F]Certainly, it might be a good opportunity to start
something. However... when I remember that man's
'lewd gaze', I can't help but hesitate.
\n<Minato>\F[\V[2]]\FF[61]\AA[F]......Can I ask you one thing?

\F[\V[2]]\FF[61]\AA[F]......Maybe he wanted to encourage me when I was feeling
down.
\n<Minato>\F[\V[2]]\FF[61]\AA[F]...Sonoda-san, do you want to see 'Actress Minato Neon'?

After thinking for a moment, \# nodded firmly. That was
enough... because it had always been that way.

Before I met \#, I was solely pursuing my music career
with passion. Even now, I believe that my passion
hasn't diminished, but I have come to realize the
existence of a driving force that surpasses it.

\#I want to continue being his ideal... I want to
continue being his number one. It's not because of
the gratitude he taught me about this world. Just
thinking about it makes my whole body feel itchy,
but simply put... in other words, it's like
this----...
\#----... The power of a love-struck maiden is unbeatable.
September 14th
